                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-14T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 14, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 14—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>461. Department’s telegram 339, December 12, noon. Matter was taken up with
                    Foreign Office November 25th and inquiry has since been made and today in reply
                    to further inquiry the Embassy was informed that the Foreign Office is not yet
                    able to make any comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
